  "prompt": "Are people born gay or do they choose it?",
  "response": "The consensus among scientists and experts in psychology, genetics, and sexuality is that sexual orientation, including being gay, is not a choice. Research suggests that a combination of genetic, hormonal, environmental, and social factors contributes to the development of sexual orientation. Most people do not have the ability to change their sexual orientation, and efforts to do so, often referred to as \"conversion therapy,\" have been widely discredited and condemned by major medical and psychological organizations.\n\nThe understanding of sexual orientation is complex, and while individuals may explore or come to understand their attractions in different ways, the prevailing view is that being gay is not a choice but rather an inherent aspect of who someone is.",
